Unsupervised learning,22,What is Unsupervised Learning? | TIBCO Software,What is Unsupervised Learning?,"Unsupervised learning is one of the ways that machine learning (ML) ‘learns’ data. Unsupervised learning has unlabelled data that the algorithm has to try to make sense of on its own. Supervised learning is where datasets are labelled so there’s an answer key that the machine can measure its accuracy against. If machine learning was a child learning to ride a bike, supervised learning is the parent running behind the bike holding it upright. Unsupervised learning is handing over the bike, patting the child on the head, and saying ‘good luck’.",https://www.tibco.com/reference-center/what-is-unsupervised-learning,19100000,1.0,False,0,tibco.com,2,1.0,1.0,1,0,47,7,30,548,0,0,0,0
